This paper is primarily focused on computer vision, specifically video object segmentation, which falls under the cs.CV sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques, such as convolutional networks, which are commonly used in the cs.LG sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new training strategy, which involves generating in-domain training data, which could fall under the cs.AI sub-category. The paper also evaluates its approach on multiple datasets, which could fall under the cs.MM sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of its approach in robotics, which could fall under the cs.RO sub-category.
